===Etymology===
{{Han compound|水|每|c1=s|c2=p|alt1=氵|t1=water|ls=psc}}

The Old Chinese word is believed to have been pronounced very much like 每, with an m- initial. [http://lodel.ehess.fr/crlao/document.php?id=1217 Baxter-Sagart] reconstruct the Old Chinese as *[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|m̥ˤəʔ]]; compare with 每 *[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|mˤəʔ]].

Appears with [[母]] (2 dots) in Chinese, yielding {{Hani|海}}, but with simplified form [[毋]] (1 cross stroke) in Japanese shinjitai, yielding {{Jpan|海}} = 氵 + [[毎]]. These are however encoded with the same Unicode character – see {{w|Han unification}}.

